漩涡中的红十字会。
Red Cross in the whirlpool.
饶贤君2020-02-06 20:29。
Rap Yin Jun 2020-02-06 20: 29.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察报 记者 饶贤君 连续多日，湖北省和武汉市红会的物资运筹效率备受质疑，2月4日，湖北省纪委监委通报，对省红十字会有关领导和干部在疫情防控期间接收和分配捐赠款物工作中存在的失职失责问题，予以严肃问责。
On February 4, Hubei Provincial Disciplinary Committee (Hubei Provincial Disciplinary Committee) issued a notice of serious accountability for negligence in the work of the leaders and cadres of the provincial Red Cross in receiving and distributing donations and goods during the period of epidemic prevention and control.
。
.
红十字会的职责是什么？此次湖北和武汉红会没能有效履责的原因又是什么呢？。
What is the responsibility of the Red Cross? What are the reasons why Hubei and Wuhan Red Cross Society failed to perform their duties effectively this time?
一次捐赠。
One donation.
“医院的朋友问我，物资到哪了，我跟她说，到红十字会仓库了，她给我回复了一个哭泣的表情。
"My friend at the hospital asked me where the supplies were, and I told her she was at the Red Cross warehouse and she gave me a sob look.
”唐琦回忆，看到那个流着两行泪的微信表情时，心里仿佛被扎了一下。
When Tang Qi recalled seeing the small letter with the two lines of tears in it, it felt as if he had been stabbed.
。
.
1月27日，唐琦的好友在朋友圈求助，请有渠道的朋友为她所在的第五医院采购口罩、医用防护服、消毒液等物资。
On January 27, Tang Qi's friends in the circle of friends for help, the channel of friends for her Fifth Hospital to purchase masks, medical protective clothing, disinfectant and other materials.
。
.
在武汉生活近20年的唐琦很快行动起来，利用自己开办旅行社的资源，联系了位于越南的几家医疗器械工厂，并与近百名朋友一起筹措了30余万元人民币，从越南工厂订购了医疗物资，由当地地接社协调带回国内。
Tang Qi, who has lived in Wuhan for nearly 20 years, quickly set about using the resources of his travel agency to contact several medical equipment factories in Vietnam and raised more than 300,000 yuan with nearly 100 friends.
。
.
受疫情影响，飞往武汉的航班全部停运，这批物资辗转多个城市到达唐琦手中，1月30日凌晨两点多，唐琦和两名捐赠人一起带着物资，奔赴武汉。
Affected by the outbreak, all flights to Wuhan, the goods transfer through a number of cities into the hands of Tang Qi, January 30 more than 2 a.m., Tang Qi and two donors together with supplies, rushed to Wuhan.
。
.
路上，唐琦多方了解得知当时的捐赠流程：医院先将所需物资上报给疫情指挥中心，捐赠人填写物资定向捐赠函，出具物资相关合格证明、票据，然后由红十字会确定接收捐赠物资，进行统一调配。
On the way, Tang Qi learned of the donation process: the hospital will first report the required materials to the epidemic command center, the donor filled out a targeted donation letter, issued material-related eligibility certificates, bills, and then the Red Cross confirmed the receipt of donated materials, unified deployment.
。
.
“有朋友告诉我，定向捐赠还要走关系开介绍信，医院才能领到物资，我当时想，先把东西送到再说。
"A friend of mine told me that targeted donations had to be accompanied by a letter of introduction before the hospital could get the supplies.
”事实证明，唐琦想当然了，从省界开始，“没有通行证，说什么都不让过”。
As it turned out, Tang Qi took it for granted, starting with the provincial boundaries, "No pass, nothing ever happened."
。
.
这期间，他多次拨打武汉市红十字会及湖北省红十字会电话，希望得到通关帮助，但在得到“我会帮你反映”的回复之后，没了下文。
During this time, he repeatedly called Wuhan Red Cross and Hubei Red Cross, hoping to get customs help, but after getting "I will help you," the response, no follow-up.
。
.
最后，一名当地相关机构的工作人员为他们送来了通行证，从湖北省高速省界到武汉国博仓库，不到80公里的路，唐琦花了13个多小时。
Finally, a staff member of the relevant local agency sent them a laissez-passer, which took more than 13 hours from the Hubei Province high-speed province boundary to the Wuhan Gobo warehouse, less than 80 kilometres away.
。
.
几名志愿者帮助唐琦卸货，唐琦注意到，仓库处停着很多辆车，一批穿着医生服装的人和几个物流工作人员围着一名红十字会工作人员，言辞有些激烈。
Several volunteers helped Tang Qi unload the goods. Tang Qi noticed that there were many cars parked in the warehouse. A group of people dressed in doctor's clothes and several logistics workers surrounded a Red Cross worker.
。
.
一名志愿者告诉唐琦，这些车都是缺物资的医院派来的，等了好几个小时没有拿到物资，红十字会工作人员没有接到通知有物资分配给这些医院，让他们回去等消息，他们不愿意回去。
A volunteer told Tang Qi that the vehicles had been sent from hospitals lacking supplies, that they had not received supplies for several hours, that Red Cross staff had not been notified of the distribution of supplies to the hospitals and that they were unwilling to return.
。
.
与唐琦同行的一位捐赠者问工作人员：“我们的物资是给五院的，他们什么时候能来取？需要介绍信吗？我们这些运送捐赠物资的志愿者还能出武汉吗？能不能给我们开一个证明让我们回去？”。
A donor accompanying Tang Qi asked the staff: "When will they be able to pick up our supplies for the five courts? Will they need a letter of introduction? Can we volunteers who deliver donations still go out of Wuhan? Can we get a certificate to go back?"
工作人员回应：物资给谁不是你们说了算的，武汉各个医院都缺物资，捐赠给哪个医院都是在做贡献。
Staff response: It is not up to you to decide to whom the supplies to, Wuhan hospitals are short of supplies, donated to which hospital are all contributing.
。
.
唐琦提出想做定向捐赠，工作人员回答，这种时候不要添乱。
Don't make a fuss at a time when Tang Qi is offering to make a targeted donation, officials said.
“我当时觉得也有道理，我们的物资数量不多，红十字会应该更专业更了解情况，交给他们分配应该没事。
"I thought it made sense that our supplies were small and that the Red Cross should be more professional and better informed, and that it should be fine to give them distribution.
”唐琦说。
"said Tang Qi.
。
.
因为不懂流程，唐琦等人卸完货，在仓库等了一会儿，“不知道还有没有什么手续要办，等了一会儿也没有人理我们，我们就开车走了。
Because do not know the process, Tang Qi and others unload goods, waiting for a while in the warehouse, "I do not know if there are any procedures to do, waiting for a while no one paid attention to us, we drove away.
”。
"
当晚，那位五院的朋友询问物资情况，唐琦如实回答，隔了半个多小时，对方回复了一个哭泣的表情，没有再说什么。
That night, the five hospital friends asked about the material situation, Tang Qi truthfully replied, more than half an hour apart, the other side replied to a crying expression, no further.
。
.
直到2月5日，唐琦还没有查到自己捐赠的那批物资是否到达五院，他和两名捐赠人目前还在武汉进行自我隔离。
Until Feb. 5, Tang Qi has not found out whether his donation to the five hospitals, he and two donors are still in Wuhan for self-isolation.
。
.
红会之职。
The Red Cross.
2月4日，湖北省纪委监委公开通报，对省红十字会有关领导和干部在疫情防控期间接收和分配捐赠款物工作中存在的失职失责问题，予以严肃问责。
On February 4, the Disciplinary Commission of Hubei Province publicly informed the public that the leaders and cadres of the provincial Red Cross Society had been seriously held accountable for their negligence in receiving and distributing donations and goods during the period of epidemic prevention and control.
。
.
问责对象为省红十字会党组成员、专职副会长张钦，省红十字会党组成员陈波，以及省红十字会党组书记、常务副会长高勤。
Accountability for members of the Provincial Red Cross party group, full-time vice-president Zhang Qin, the Provincial Red Cross party group member Chen Bo, and the Provincial Red Cross Secretary, Standing Vice-President Gao Qin.
。
.
此前，湖北省红十字会官网信息显示，除张钦、陈波、高勤外，湖北省红十字会的领导还包括湖北省人民政府党组成员、副省长、湖北省红十字会会长赵海山，湖北省红十字会二级巡视员邓红，目前，该列表中已经没有张钦的名字。
In addition to Zhang Qin, Chen Bo and Gao, Hubei Red Cross leaders include Zhao Haishan, vice-governor of the Hubei Provincial People's Government, Zhao Haishan, head of the Hubei Red Cross Society, and Deng Hong, a second-class inspector of the Hubei Red Cross.
。
.
官网信息还显示，包括五人的领导班子在内，湖北省红十字会日常工作人员约有20人，共有四个正处级机构，分别是办公室、赈济救护部、组织宣传部、监事会工作部，此外还设有三个直属事业单位，分别为中国红十字会湖北备灾救灾中心、中国造血干细胞捐献者资料库湖北分库管理中心以及湖北省人体器官捐献管理中心。
The official website also shows that the staff of the Red Cross Society in Hubei Province, including the five-member leadership team, has about 20 regular staff, including offices, relief and rescue department, organizational publicity department and supervisory board work department.
。
.
赈济救护部负责全省红十字会系统备灾救灾、自救互救培训、人道救助的“三救”日常工作；针对突发公共事件和自然灾害的应急救助和救护工作；统筹、协调、指导和实施境内外资金支持的项目工作以及开展募捐筹资活动等。
The Relief Department is responsible for the daily work of the provincial Red Cross Society in disaster preparedness and relief, mutual self-help training and humanitarian relief; emergency relief and rescue work in response to sudden public events and natural disasters; plans, coordinates, guides and implements projects supported by domestic and foreign funds, and conducts fund-raising activities.
。
.
办公室主要负责内部工作协调、文秘、人事管理、后勤管理、信息化建设等内务工作；组织宣传部负责基层组织的相关法规、政策建设宣传，志愿者队伍建设、管理、培训，红十字会知识、人道法传播等内外宣传发展工作。
The Office is mainly responsible for internal coordination, secretarial work, personnel administration, logistics management, information technology and other internal affairs work. It organizes the Ministry of Information to publicize the relevant regulations and policies of grass-roots organizations, build up, manage and train volunteer corps, disseminate knowledge of the Red Cross and humanitarian law.
。
.
而《2018年度武汉市红十字会部门决算》文件则显示，武汉市红十字会设有三个内部机构，分别是业务部、办公室和遗体捐献管理中心，总编制人数13人，实际在职12人，参照公务员法管理11人，主要应对紧急情况、备灾救灾的部门为业务部。
According to the 2018 Wuhan Red Cross Departmental Accounts, the Wuhan Red Cross Society has three internal organizations, namely, the Operations Department, the Office and the Monument Donation Management Center.
。
.
此外，湖北省红十字会及武汉市红十字会均在官网上有如下描述：为最困难、最需要、最易受损人群提供人道服务，历史悠久，功在人间。
The Red Cross Society of Hubei Province and the Wuhan Red Cross Society both wrote on the official website that they have a long history of providing humanitarian services to the most difficult, needy and vulnerable groups.
。
.
缺位。
Not available.
1月26日，民政部指定湖北省红十字会、湖北省慈善总会、湖北省青少年发展基金会、武汉市慈善总会、武汉市红十字会5家牵头，接收慈善组织为湖北省武汉市疫情防控工作募集的款物。
On January 26, the Ministry of Civil Affairs designated the Hubei Red Cross Society, Hubei Provincial Charitable General Association, Hubei Provincial Youth Development Foundation, Wuhan Municipal Charitable General Association and Wuhan City Red Cross Society to take the lead in receiving money and goods collected by charitable organizations for the prevention and control of the epidemic in Wuhan, Hubei Province.
。
.
然而，口罩分配事件、为领导取口罩等一连串事件的曝光，将两大红会送上风口浪尖。
However, the distribution of masks and the exposure of a series of events, such as the wearing of a mask for the leader, will send the two big red ones to the fore.
。
.
被问责前，张钦接受媒体专访时表示，省红十字会面临的主要问题是人员少，在岗的只有21个人。
In an interview with the media before being held accountable, Zhang said the main problem facing the provincial Red Cross was its small staff, with only 21 people on duty.
。
.
《中国慈善家》对湖北红会的专访中，相关负责人也表示：在这种重大的突发性公共卫生疫情面前，到底是怎么作为、怎么样去配合政府作为？一直有变化，我们也不太清楚。
In an interview with the Hubei Red Cross Society, China Philanthropists also said: In the face of such a major public health emergency, how to act and how to cooperate with the government? We have been changing, we are not very clear.
有时候我们跟不上政府信息的一些发布和传播，可能也有一个调整的过程，包括社会舆论，有一些是是非非的东西，一些爱心人士也觉得很迷茫。
Sometimes we can't keep up with the release and dissemination of government information. There may also be a process of adjustment, including public opinion.
作为我们来讲已经是心力交瘁，但是在这个位置上你还得坚持。
It's exhausting for us, but you have to stick to it.
。
.
湖北当地公益组织的一位负责人表示，缺人手是现实存在的状况，从1月23日武汉封城开始，红十字会就开始和各个公益组织联系，寻求志愿者支援，“要接电话、搬物资、统计善款，红十字会自己的人手根本不够”。
A head of a local public welfare organization in Hubei province said the shortage of staff was a reality. Since the city was closed on January 23 in Wuhan, the Red Cross has been contacting various public welfare organizations for volunteer support.
。
.
一位了解红十字会内部管理体系的人士表示，中国的红十字会是“类政府机关”，专职人员属于国家事业单位编制；财务上由国家财政拨款，参照公务员待遇；在重大灾害、突发事件时，政府指导、指派红十字会组织募捐事宜。
A person familiar with the Red Cross internal management system said that the Red Cross Society in China is a "government-like organ," with full-time staff drawn up by state institutions.
。
.
该人士介绍，国际红十字会通常会汇集不同领域的人士，组成理事会、监事会等机构，负责募捐、监督等职能，具体捐赠、善款管理等会在社会上聘请专业度高的专职人员负责，各司其职，平时也高度重视志愿者团队的建设，遇到重大事件，能够快速反应。
The International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) will normally bring together people from different fields to form a board of directors, a supervisory board and other agencies to raise funds, supervise and manage donations.
。
.
早在2018年12月3日，国务院印发了《中国红十字会总会改革方案》，对中国红十字会提出改革措施，其中包括优化机构设置，完善理事会、常务理事会制度，增设监事会；改革组织人事制度，改进干部选拔任用工作；加强公信力建设，成立与社会化接轨的智库体系、善用互联网、推进公开透明等。
As early as December 3, 2018, the State Council issued the Reform Program of the Chinese Red Cross Society, proposing reform measures to the Chinese Red Cross, including optimizing the institutional set-up, improving the council and general council system and adding supervisory board.
。
.
此后，各省市也推进了相应的改革方案，2019年6月，湖北省委书记蒋超良主持召开省委全面深化改革委员会第三次会议，审议通过了《湖北省红十字会改革方案》，方案提及五方面17条改革措施，基本与红十字总会改革方案一致，其中包括“打造具有公信力的专业化人道公益服务平台”。
In June 2019, the Third Meeting of the Provincial Committee on Comprehensive and Deepening Reform was held under the chairmanship of the secretary of the Hubei Provincial Party Committee, Jiang Xiaoliang.
。
.
从此次“战疫”的表现看，改革仍有待落实，人民网湖北频道发表了如下评论：除了警示，更应该反思，红会在遇到重大公共突发事件时，有没有相应的应急预案，或者现有的应急预案还能否适应新的形势、新的要求、新的任务，特别是能否适应和满足人民群众的新期待。
According to the performance of the epidemic, the reform still needs to be carried out. Hubei channel of the People's Network issued the following comments: Apart from warning, the Red Cross should also reflect on whether it has an emergency plan in case of major public emergencies or whether the existing emergency plans can adapt to the new situation, new requirements and new tasks, especially whether it can meet the new expectations of the people.
人员方面必然捉襟见肘，但是如何来调控、分配和招聘，以应对满负荷甚至超负荷的工作状态，都需要检视反思和完善改进。
The human side is certainly overstretched, but how to regulate, allocate and recruit to deal with a full load or even overload of work requires review and improvement.
。
.
